sentences: Avi Buffalo (born Avigdor Benyamin Zahner-Isenberg, November 5, 1990) is an American musician, songwriter, and producer.
Avi Buffalo's self-titled debut album was released on April 27, 2010, and was given positive reviews by The A.V. Club, NME, Filter, Drowned in Sound and numerous other music review sites.
His band performed at SXSW the same year, and opened for Modest Mouse in July.

Avi began recording a follow-up to his self-titled album in 2012, and in 2013 began producing other artists and side projects in addition to his own material.

In 2015, he said he was putting an end to the band Avi Buffalo.
In 2019, he released the electronic album Glow Cast on Eternal Sound with Ari Prado.
On July 27, 2020, Avi Buffalo was accused of rape by a former bandmate.
